title: SPY Presents: Loretta Lynn's Amateur National 2011
description: The Spy amateur mx team recently spent the week at the 30th annual RedBull Loretta Lynn's MX national in Hurricane Mills, TN. This is the biggest amateur race in the world with the highest talent in amateur motocross. Spy Optic won two championships throughout the week with Chris Plouffe taking the open pro sport title, and Blake Green winning the 12-14 85cc stock title!! Mitchell Falk won a moto in his first trip to the ranch in the 9-11 65cc class and Derek Drake finished up 4th and 5th overall in the 9-11 65cc stock and modified classes. KTM Orange Brigade team manager Mike Sleeter finished up 3rd overall in the 25+ pro class.
